<subSubSection pageId="71" pageNumber="72" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="71.[151,1437,151,1293]" box="[199,914,1159,1184]" pageId="71" pageNumber="72">• Surface conulose and honeycomb-like, with exposed fibres.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="71.[151,1437,151,1293]" pageId="71" pageNumber="72">• Secondary fibres uncored, more prevalent near the ectosome. Collagen deposits present within the mesohyl, but only minor deposits at the surface.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="71.[151,1437,151,1293]" box="[199,551,1268,1293]" pageId="71" pageNumber="72">• Emerald green colouration.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
